uv print on glass spheres on alu dibond. 63 x 90cm, 2026.<br>9, 10.  <em>After Discipline</em>, sd video and sound, 49 min. 2023. Film Still.</p><div class=\"image-gallery-embed\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;gallery&quot;:{&quot;images&quot;:[{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/c99dbb0b-0b94-45ef-ba29-b39e8300969c_1534x2300.jpeg&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/24fafdaf-10e0-4cf6-adc8-d31874d3b22c_1534x2300.jpeg&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/8e89ce70-bbe8-4773-a95f-acd1a7e0c964_2300x1534.jpeg&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/42e0fbe7-795b-490e-82c4-d935b3e854c3_2300x1534.jpeg&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/bf54bb58-c4c1-44a7-aa00-1e432900c1dd_2300x1534.jpeg&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/da0f0b96-f042-4bdb-a84a-c95d5bb0c73b_2300x1534.jpeg&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/e1d49e10-159b-4813-89a2-f15fb8098be6_1534x2300.jpeg&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/0ff3f4de-245e-44cc-a8d6-10605ad10370_1534x2300.jpeg&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/5f19a1a2-aebf-45db-9511-f2ed6325123b_1534x2300.jpeg&quot;}],&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;Photo Credit: Kim? Contemporary Art Centre and photos by: Ansis Starks, 2026&quot;,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;staticGalleryImage&quot;:{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/2c37b114-7285-4b76-a25a-79c6993b3fd4_1456x1454.png&quot;}},&quot;isEditorNode&quot;:true}\"></div><p>Description of this show sourced from the official website:</p><p>EDEN: Wet Work Over Lap stages desire as labor and sex as one of its most regulated, exhausted, and persistently unfinished forms. The title, EDEN: Wet Work Over Lap, draws on the double meaning of “wet work,” referring both to covert operations and to forms of labor that leave a trace. It is these practices and artworks which expand sexual, emotional, and domestic work into modes of maintenance that accumulate, rather than resolve, into meaning. “Over Lap” signals repetition and spill, where actions do not conclude but instead extend across time, overlapping, leaking, and returning.</p><p>With new and existing art works, installations, and performances spanning from analogue processes to “digital wetwares”, EDEN: Wet Work Over Lap sustains the infrastructure of desire through exhibition areas associatively shifting between functional sites: bedroom-after hour zone into auditorium, bathroom-wet room into confessional, gym into club into darkroom - all towards a central hall (“aktu zāle”), carrying the double meaning of “akts”, act and nude, finally climaxing in an exhibitionary attempt to center the concept of exposure as both a performance and condition at once.</p>"
